io.logspace.hq.core.api.model

Interface Spaces

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SpacesImpl

    public interface Spaces
    Spaces are used to distinguish events from different sources.
    To ensure some basic authentication for a space, authenticationTokens must be configured for a space, which consumers must supply as an authenticationToken to store their events.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      String getSpaceForAuthenticationToken(String authenticationToken)
      Retrieve the space for the supplied authenticationToken.

      • getSpaceForAuthenticationToken

        String getSpaceForAuthenticationToken(String authenticationToken)
        Retrieve the space for the supplied authenticationToken.
        Parameters:
        authenticationToken - - The supplied authenticationToken.
        Returns:
        The space for the authenticationToken or null if no space is configured for this token.
